-- Wales Wins Six Nations Rugby Grand Slam by Beating France 16-9
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-03-17T16:33:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/wales-wins-six-nations-rugby-grand-slam-by-beating-france-16-9.html
Wales  beat France 16-9 to complete
the Grand Slam in rugby’s Six Nations championship.  Alex Cuthbert scored a try and Leigh Halfpenny kicked 11
points for Wales, which won all five of its games in the
tournament -- known as the Grand Slam -- to capture the title
for the first time since 2008. It’s the third Grand Slam for the
Welsh since the Six Nations format began in 2000.  Italy beat Scotland 13-6 earlier, while  England  hosts
Ireland later in the tournament’s final match.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  